alse,","+\t\t\texpectError:          false,","+\t\t},","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:                 \"type=helm with enable-oci and insecure-oci-force-http\",","+\t\t\tinsecureOCIForceHTTP: true,","+\t\t\trepoType:             \"helm\",","+\t\t\tenableOCI:            true,","+\t\t\texpectError:          false,","+\t\t},","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:                 \"type=helm without enable-oci and insecure-oci-force-http\",","+\t\t\tinsecureOCIForceHTTP: true,","+\t\t\trepoType:             \"helm\",","+\t\t\tenableOCI:            false,","+\t\t\texpectError:          true,","+\t\t},","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:                 \"type=git with insecure-oci-force-http\",","+\t\t\tinsecureOCIForceHTTP: true,","+\t\t\trepoType:             \"git\",","+\t\t\tenableOCI:            false,","+\t\t\texpectError:          true,","+\t\t},","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:                 \"type=git with enable-oci and insecure-oci-force-http\",","+\t\t\tinsecureOCIForceHTTP: true,","+\t\t\trepoType:             \"git\",","+\t\t\tenableOCI:            true,","+\t\t\texpectError:          true,","+\t\t},","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:                 \"insecure-oci-force-http not set on git repo\",","+\t\t\tinsecureOCIForceHTTP: false,","+\t\t\trepoType:             \"git\",","+\t\t\tenableOCI:            false,","+\t\t\texpectError:          false,","+\t\t},","+\t\t{","+\t\t\tname:                 \"insecure-oci-force-http not set on helm repo\",","+\t\t\tinsecureOCIForceHTTP: false,","+\t\t\trepoType:             \"helm\",","+\t\t\tenableOCI:            false,","+\t\t\texpectError:          false,","+\t\t},","+\t}","+\tfor _, tt := range tests {","+\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {","+\t\t\terr := ValidateInsecureOCIForceHTTP(tt.insecureOCIForceHTTP, tt.repoType, tt.enableOCI)","+\t\t\tif tt.expectError {","+\t\t\t\trequire.ErrorContains(t, err, \"--insecure-oci-force-http requires --type oci or --enable-oci\")","+\t\t\t} else {","+\t\t\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)","+\t\t\t}","+\t\t})","+\t}","+}"],"additions":70,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"docs/operator-manual/upgrading/3.4-3.5.md","lines":["@@ -2,6 +2,47 @@"," "," ## Breaking Changes"," ","+###  Helm was upgraded to `4.2.0`. ","+","+In Helm v4, the OCI implementation is more strict: if the registry doesn't speak TLS, it is required to explicitly use `--plain-http` upon `helm push`, `helm registry login` and upon `helm dependency build`. ","+","+This is a breaking change for Argo CD users with plain HTTP OCI registries. Two actions may be required:","+","+#### Set --insecure-oci-force-http on existing OCI repos","+","+For any existing OCI repository that uses plain HTTP (not HTTPS), add the flag via CLI (CLI version 3.5): `repo add ... --insecure-oci-force-http --upsert`   ","+Or set it directly in the Kubernetes secret:","+```yaml","+stringData:","+   insecureOCIForceHttp: \"true\"","+```","+","+#### Explicitly register plain HTTP dependency repos","+","+If your Helm charts have OCI dependencies (Chart.yaml dependencies with repository: `oci://...`) hosted on plain HTTP registries, those dependency repos must now be explicitly added to Argo CD with the `--insecure-oci-force-http` flag, the same way as described above. With Helm v3 this was not required — plain HTTP OCI dependency registries were accessed transparently without registration. With Helm v4, Argo CD needs to know which dependency registries use plain HTTP in order to pass `--plain-http` to `helm dependency build`.","+","+#### Known limitation — conflicting TLS flags (Helm v4)","+","+For Argo CD OCI repo, setting both `--insecure-skip-server-verification` (passed to Helm as `--insecure-skip-tls-verify`) and `--insecure-oci-force-http` (passed to Helm as `--plain-http`) causes Helm v4 to silently drop `--plain-http`, as `--insecure-skip-tls-verify` takes internal precedence. Plain HTTP registry operations then fail with `http: server gave HTTP response to HTTPS client`. This affects:","+","+- Argo CD repos with `type=helm` with `--enable-oci`: having both flags on the same repo causes the chart pull to fail.","+- Argo CD repos with `type=oci` and `type=helm` with dependencies: `--insecure-skip-server-verification` on the main repo combined with `--insecure-oci-force-http` on any dependency repo causes dependency build to fail.","+","+There is no workaround when both configurations are legitimately required in the same chain. ","+","+#### Applications with spec.source.helm.version setting","+","+If you historically have the following setting on your Helm application, the setting is ignored and Argo CD will use Helm v4 only to render your charts:","+","+```yaml","+spec:","+  source:","+    helm:","+      version: v3","+```","+","+You are not required to update or remove this field, and can leave this setting as is.","+"," ### UI extensions must externalize `react/jsx-runtime`"," "," The Argo CD UI was upgraded from React 16 to React 19 in 3.5. UI extensions built against an older Argo CD UI may fail to load with a `TypeError` until they are rebuilt to externalize `react/jsx-runtime`.","@@ -130,6 +171,8 @@ Consume structured result from `sourceIntegrityResult` field instead."," "," ## Helm Upgraded"," ","+Helm was upgraded to `4.2.0`, resulting in some breaking changes described in the `Breaking changes` section of this doc.","+"," ## Custom Healthchecks Added"," "," ## Other Changes"],"additions":43,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"docs/user-guide/commands/argocd_repocreds_add.md","lines":["@@ -56,6 +56,7 @@ argocd repocreds add REPOURL [flags]","       --github-app-installation-id int                 installation id of the GitHub Application (optional, will be auto-discovered if not provided)","       --github-app-private-key-path string             private key of the GitHub Application","   -h, --help                                           help for add","+      --insecure-oci-force-http                        Use http when accessing an OCI repository","       --password string                                password to the repository","       --proxy-url string                               If provided, this URL will be used to connect via proxy","       --ssh-private-key-path string                    path to the private ssh key (e.g. ~/.ssh/id_rsa)"],"additions":1,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"docs/user-guide/helm.md","lines":["@@ -689,18 +689,14 @@ repoServer:","           chmod -R 777 $HELM_DATA_HOME;"," ```"," ","-## Helm Version","+## Helm Version "," ","-Argo CD will assume that the Helm chart is v3 (even if the apiVersion field in the chart is Helm v2), unless v2 is explicitly specified within the Argo CD Application (see below).","+This field was used in the past, during the transition period from Helm 2 to Helm 3.","+Before Helm 2 became EOL, Argo CD was shipped with both Helm binaries (v2 and v3) and users could specify which Helm binary Argo CD should use to render their charts, by setting this field."," ","-If needed, it is possible to specifically set the Helm version to template with by setting the `helm-version` flag on the cli (either v2 or v3):","-","-```bash","-argocd app set helm-guestbook --helm-version v3","-```","-","-Or using declarative syntax:","+Since Helm 2 became EOL, this field does not need to be configured anymore. It exists for backwards-compatibility only. The only Helm binary used to render charts in Argo CD (starting with version 3.5) is v4."," ","+If you historically have the following setting on your Helm applications:"," ```yaml"," spec:","   source:","@@ -708,6 +704,9 @@ spec:","       version: v3"," ```"," ","+you are not required to update or remove this field, and can leave this setting as is.","+","+"," ## Helm `--pass-credentials`"," "," Helm, [starting with v3.6.1](https://github.com/helm/helm/releases/tag/v3.6.1),"],"additions":8,"deletions":9,"truncated":false},{"path":"hack/installers/checksums/helm-v4.2.0-darwin-amd64.tar.gz.sha256","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1 @@","+1376ea697140e4db316736e760d